<subSubSection box="[151,836,1901,1925]" pageId="29" pageNumber="330" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,836,1901,1925]" box="[151,836,1901,1925]" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,291,1901,1925]" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">
<typeStatus box="[151,204,1901,1925]" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority=", Reed, 1917" authorityName=", Reed" authorityYear="1917" box="[298,616,1901,1925]" class="Trilobita" family="Pliomeridae" genus="Pliomera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phacopida" pageId="29" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martellii">
<emphasis box="[298,485,1901,1925]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">Pliomera martellii</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Reed, F. R. C." box="[498,616,1901,1925]" pageId="29" pageNumber="330" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref46843" refString="Reed, F. R. C. (1917) Ordovician and Silurian fossils from Yun-nan. Palaeontologia Indica, 6 (3), 1 - 69." type="journal article" year="1917">Reed, 1917</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="331" pageId="29" pageNumber="330" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,1971,2034]" lastBlockId="30.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="331" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,284,1971,1997]" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">Discussion.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[341,389,1972,1998]" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chugaeva" authorityYear="1956" box="[514,640,1971,1997]" class="Trilobita" family="Pliomeridae" genus="Pliomerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phacopida" pageId="29" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[514,640,1971,1997]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">Pliomerina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is part of Reed’s collection, but this is known only from the cranidium, redescribed here. Silicified and complete material from 
<collectingCountry box="[784,887,2007,2033]" name="Australia" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">Australia</collectingCountry>
described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Webby, B. D. E." box="[1047,1201,2007,2033]" pageId="29" pageNumber="330" pagination="612 - 622" refId="ref48301" refString="Webby, B. D. E. (1971) The Ordovician trilobite Pliomerina Chugaeva from the Ordovician of New South Wales. Palaeontology, 14, 612 - 622." type="journal article" year="1971">Webby (1971</bibRefCitation>
, p. 614) is doubtless congeneric with the 
<collectingCountry box="[381,490,151,177]" name="Myanmar" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
<typeStatus box="[498,546,151,177]" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">type</typeStatus>
species, and provides a fuller diagnosis than is possible from the 
<typeStatus box="[1289,1337,151,177]" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">type</typeStatus>
material alone. 
<bibRefCitation author="Webby, B. D. E." box="[227,388,187,213]" pageId="30" pageNumber="331" pagination="612 - 622" refId="ref48301" refString="Webby, B. D. E. (1971) The Ordovician trilobite Pliomerina Chugaeva from the Ordovician of New South Wales. Palaeontology, 14, 612 - 622." type="journal article" year="1971">Webby (1971)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chugaeva" authorityYear="1956" box="[584,710,187,213]" class="Trilobita" family="Pliomeridae" genus="Pliomerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phacopida" pageId="30" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[584,710,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">Pliomerina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed across Australasia and adjacent territories, extending from 
<collectingCountry box="[328,459,223,249]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
in the north to 
<collectingRegion box="[627,828,223,249]" country="Australia" name="New South Wales" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">New South Wales</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[836,942,223,249]" name="Australia" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">Australia</collectingCountry>
, in the south, with additional occurrences on the South 
<collectingCountry box="[264,331,259,285]" name="China" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">China</collectingCountry>
plate, Sibumasu and 
<collectingCountry box="[570,641,259,285]" name="South Korea" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">Korea</collectingCountry>
, i.e. palaeotropical Gondwana on current palaeocontinental reconstructions. Webby preferred the term “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chugaeva" authorityYear="1956" box="[522,648,295,321]" class="Trilobita" family="Pliomeridae" genus="Pliomerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phacopida" pageId="30" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[522,648,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">Pliomerina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fauna” to cover this Ordovician biogeographic region to “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reed" authorityYear="1915" box="[1294,1436,295,321]" class="Trilobita" family="Pliomeridae" genus="Encrinurella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phacopida" pageId="30" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1294,1436,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">Encrinurella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fauna” coined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Whittington, H. B. &amp; Hughes, C. P." box="[348,687,331,357]" pageId="30" pageNumber="331" pagination="236 - 276" refId="ref48641" refString="Whittington, H. B. &amp; Hughes, C. P. (1972) Ordovician geography and faunal provinces. Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London, Series B, 263, 236 - 276. https: // doi. org / 10.1098 / rstb. 1972.0001" type="journal article" year="1972">Whittington &amp; Hughes (1972)</bibRefCitation>
, though they embrace a similar geographic compass. 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhou, Z. - Y. &amp; Zhen, Y. - Y." pageId="30" pageNumber="331" refId="ref49762" refString="Zhou, Z. - Y. &amp; Zhen, Y. - Y. (Eds.) (2008) Trilobite Record of China. Science Press, Beijing, 20 pp." type="book" year="2008">Zhou &amp; Zhen (2008)</bibRefCitation>
record the genus through much of the post-Tremadocian Ordovician of 
<collectingCountry box="[1044,1114,367,393]" name="China" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">China</collectingCountry>
, including northeastern Chinese and Tibetan occurrences.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
